# Wire Next.js API Route Handlers

This plan sets up the Next.js App Router API endpoints by importing the previously built backend route adapters and exporting them as standard Next.js route handlers (`GET`, `POST`, etc.). It also updates the dependencies by installing the required `server-only` package and provides an environment variables template.

## Proposed Changes

### Dependency Updates

- **Install `server-only`**: The `server-only` package is required by the `backend/config/` modules but is missing from `package.json`.

#### [NEW] `c:\download\ship_or_shink\.env.example`
Create an environment template with keys derived from `backend/config/env.config.ts`.

